LDG_OPEN(3)                   LDG Call                     LDG_OPEN(3)

NAME
    ldg_open - open a dynamical library
    
SYNOPSYS
   #include <ldg.h>

   LDG *ldg_open( char *name, WORD *global);

PARAMETERS
           name : library name (relative or complete path),
         global : global array used by AES functions,
         return : the LDG descriptor of the library or NULL if error.

DESCRIPTION
   This function loads a LDG-library in memory. If the library is  not
   in memory, it is loaded using the current directory. If library  is
   not found,  $LDGPATH  environ value,  LDG  cookie value  and  $PATH
   environ value are used to locate  the library. If an error  occurs,
   the function returns  NULL and  an explicite error  message can  be
   obtain with function ldg_error().

   When a library is loaded, the  client can received a message  (from
   LDG kernel),  LDG_QUIT, which  indicates a  library loaded  by  the
   client has  been removed  from  the memory.  In this  case,  client
   should reload the library. The message has the following structure:   

        word 0   : LDG_QUIT
        word 1-2 : unused
        word 3-4 : address of the LDG-descriptor
        word 5   : raison of the terminaison :
                    0 : shutdown
                    1 : screen resolution changed
                    2 : crashed or explicit terminaison of the library
  

COMPATIBILITY LDG 1.xx
   ldg_open() replaces ldg_exec(), ldg_exec_evnt(), ldg_libexec(). Macros
   defined in LDG.H emulates these functions.

SEE ALSO
   ldg_close(3), ldg_error(3).
  
